.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-CHECK" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-check \- verify wallet database integrity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-check
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs
.B PRAGMA integrity_check
on the active wallet's SQLite database, verifies that the required
tables (
.B accounts
and
.BR ledger )
exist, and reports per-table row counts.
.PP
Output on success:
.nf
{"ok":true,"tables":{"accounts":N,"ledger":N,...}}
.fi
Output on failure:
.nf
{"ok":false,"errors":["..."]}
.fi
Exits with status 1 if the database is missing or corrupt.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Database is intact.
.TP
.B 1
Database is missing or integrity check failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-stats (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-backup (1)
